== Linux Disk Space Commands

Reports the amount of available disk space being used by file systems.
Print sizes in human readable format (-h).

*df -h*

Display the amount of free space, mounting poind and etc for directory.

*df <DIRECTORY>*

Use the 'lsblk' command to view available disk devices and their mount points.

*lsblk*

Interactive process viewer.

*htop*
